headline: 3 Reasons to Avoid IR and 1 Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Since April 2025, Ingersoll Rand has been in a holding pattern, posting a small return of 2.1% while floating around $74.88. The stock also fell short of the S&P 500’s 21.1% gain during that period.
